summary:
Having a solid academic background and experience, I have gained a considerable knowledge in all aspects of electronics engineering. As a member of Istanbul Technical University (ITU) IEEE student branch in 2004, I took the responsibility of Electronics Laboratory for two years where two of my team-projects had an extensive interest to represent ITU at WIN EUROASIA Automation Exhibition. Graduated from ITU with a Bachelor of Electronics Engineering, my final year project was about the design and construction of “Solid State Tesla Coil” being the 1st & only example in Turkey. My education has provided me a variety of technical knowledge and practical skills; that is why I decided to pursue my career to take on new challenges in the industrial environment.
 
I have been employed for the past 7 years as an R&D Engineer/Manager in the development of firmware, software and discrete circuit design; besides I have provided innovative solutions by working in multi-disciplinary teams and take the companies few steps forward. My 1st professional circuit board designed while I was working part-time at TEES Company (2008) is still on the market. I have demonstrated creative thinking and problem solving skills at ZER Electronics in collaboration with the Industrial Design Team and the Production Team to prepare the final product from conceptual design for automotive and military industries. Just after my first year, I was promoted as an R&D Manager and Military Production Line Manager due to my innovative mindset and my history of successful team projects. Currently employed at a project based R&D company, Mir Ar-Ge A.S. (MIR R&D Inc.), most of my work concentrated with creating cutting edge technologies and making/ improving the final products in a cross-functional team of mechanical design, industrial design, chemistry and agriculture. Additionally, I have good writing skills and am able to create technical specifications, author manuals as well as documentation.
